snippet.textDisplay:
So he doesn't get that Artificial Humans is a thing already. Body and all having them move was the problem until now i guess. Having my human doll be linked to my Alexa devices will be kinda creepy when it happens. I am not a fan of Artificial Humans in the form they are right now as their current functions are super limited and a disembodied voice is much body for an interface. Now when holograms are able to be made from a projector and it is cheap enough to be sold on mass to everyone then we will have the black mirror episode. I do not see Amazon putting their Alexa AI into a Artificial human that is a human sized doll that looks and is able to move like a human but needs a charging station after a hour or however long they can make the battery last for. Right now the battery lasts for 4 hours but we have better battery technology than what was used in it. Just the market for a Artificial human to be there hand and foot to wait on you is not there when we have a robot to clean the floor for us, a robot to open the door, turn on / off the lights for us, to see and report what is happen in and out of our homes, report any illegal happens that are on or in our property, monitor our children for us, play with them for us, teach them to a certain extent, and of course go shopping for us to order what we say or tell us what we want based on the past of what we have ordered and when then have it come to our door some times also be put inside our home for us too.
An Artificial human was a nice thing in concept but the disembodied voice that is Alexa is better molding them together might work for some who want to think they are with a human but replacing a human with a robot is the only use case i can find for that.
